Careers

Contact the Department of Human Resources for the current openings below



Position: Admission Associates
Job Description: 
We are seeking a few admission associates to support the work of school admissions and recruitment. American Education Center assists over hundreds students per year to different levels of schools and colleges. Reporting to the Program Manager, the Admission Associates have the following responsibilities:

Assist prospective students with the application process and provide information on their chosen programs and schools;
Communicate with prospective and current students by phone, email, and in person
Maintain and enter information into multiple database systems for all applicants
Participate in the planning and implementation of recruitment events for every admission season;
Greet prospective clients and answer phone lines at the main reception desk
Perform general administrative work including word processing, database report generation, and organization of student documents

Position Qualifications:

Bachelor's degree required; preferably some graduate school; 
Experience working in a higher education setting, preferably in an advising capacity with current or potential students;
Excellent interpersonal skills and attention to detail
Proficient in MS Office programs and Google apps;
Familiar with school application procedures and have strong connection with different schools, especially top ranking universities;
Experienced in admission at Ivy League colleges is a great plus.



Interested candidates please email your resume and cover letter to hr@aec100.com or fill out our contact form.














