July 25, 2017 1:32 PM ET
Diversified Consumer Services

Company Overview of American Education Centers, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
American Education Centers, Inc. operates colleges throughout the United States. It offers degree, diploma, and certificate programs in the business, healthcare, and technology fields. The company was founded in 1993 and is based in Fort Mitchell, Kentucky. As of September 2, 2003, American Education Centers, Inc. operates as a subsidiary of Education Management Corporation.


309 Buttermilk PikeFort Mitchell, KY 41017-2138United StatesFounded in 1993



Phone: 412-995-7206

Fax: 412-995-7553








Key Executives for American Education Centers, Inc.


American Education Centers, Inc. does not have any Key Executives recorded. 



American Education Centers, Inc. Key Developments

American Education Center, Inc. Announces Auditor Changes
Jul 5 17
American Education Center, Inc. announced that on May 23, 2017, the Board of Director of the company approved the appointment of Marcum Bernstein &Pinchuk LLP as the company's independent registered public accounting firm for the company's fiscal year ending December 31, 2017, pending MarcumBP's internal approval process of client intake. Accordingly, on June 22, 2017, MarcumBP replaced Wei, Wei &Co. LLP as the independent auditors for the company with immediate effect.


